Macroscopy: pleuritis, pericarditis, sealing and pulmonary oedema
There are four types of viral pneumonia:
mild form of pneumonia: pulmonary oedema, pneumocytic hyperplasia, large atypical pneumocytes, interstitial inflammation with lymphocytic infiltration and the formation of multinuclear giant cells
severe form of pneumonia: diffuse alveolar damage (DAD) with diffuse alveolar exudate.
DAD is the cause of acute respiratory distress syndrome (ORDS) and severe hypoxemia.
Healing pneumonia: organization of exudates in the alveolar cavities and pulmonary interstitial fibrosis.
